  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria

          -  Clinical diagnosis of unresectable metastatic melanoma.

          -  No prior chemotherapy for melanoma, and no chemotherapy for other malignancies within
             5 years and at least 4 weeks since treatment (surgery, radiation, or immunotherapy)
             for melanoma.

        Exclusion Criteria

        Patients who exhibit any of the following conditions at screening will not be eligible for
        admission into the study:

          -  Any other prior malignancy, except for the following: adequately treated basal or
             squamous cell skin cancer or superficial bladder cancer, or any other cancer from
             which the patient has been disease-free for &gt;=5 years.

          -  Active autoimmune disease.

          -  Active infection requiring therapy, or chronic active HBV or HCV, or confirmed
             reactivity with HIV tests.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
